│ non-PHI instructions are still inserted at the original,     │
│ now-incorrect insertion point at the very top of the block.  │
│                                                              │
│ The correct API to use is `BasicBlock::getFirstNonPHI()`,    │
│ which returns an iterator pointing *past* all PHI nodes,     │
│ providing a safe insertion point for new computational       │
│ instructions. The name is confusingly similar, but the       │
│ behavior is critically different for our use case. The       │
│ `getFirstInsertionPt` method is more suited for cases where  │
│ you are certain no new PHIs will be added to the block after │
│ the insertion point is calculated.                           │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to replace the call to `getFirstInsertionPt()`    │
│ with `getFirstNonPHI()` to ensure new instructions are       │
│ always placed after any and all PHI nodes in the block.      │
