│ of the problem is in                                         │
│ `SCEVExpander::GetOptimalInsertionPointForCastOf`. This      │
│ function uses `BB->getFirstInsertionPt()` to find a place to │
│ insert new instructions. This method returns an iterator to  │
│ the first non-PHI instruction, which is the *start* of the   │
│ block if it only contains PHIs. When `SCEVExpander` later    │
│ adds non-PHI instructions at this point, they end up before  │
│ the PHIs, corrupting the IR. The correct method to use is    │
│ `BB->getFirstNonPHI()`, which returns an iterator to the     │
│ position *after* all PHI nodes, which is the valid insertion │
│ point for new computational instructions.\n\n### 4. Proposed │
│ Edit Point(s)\n\nTo fix this, the incorrect method call must │
│ be replaced.\n\n*   **File**:                                │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/ScalarEvolutionExpander.cpp`\n*   │
│ **Line**: 189\n*   **Change**: Replace                       │
│ `.getFirstInsertionPt()` with                                │
│ `.getFirstNonPHI()`.\n\n```cpp\n// Before:\n                 │
│ .getFirstInsertionPt();\n\n// After:\n                       │
│ .getFirstNonPHI();\n```\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nThis change  │
│ ensures that `SCEVExpander` always inserts new non-PHI       │
│ instructions at a valid point in the basic block, after any  │
│ existing PHI nodes. This prevents the generation of          │
│ malformed IR and resolves the verifier crash, making loop    │
│ unrolling with symbolic, cross-loop dependencies more        │
│ robust."                                                     │
│     }                                                        │
